cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.LG 

This paper focuses on using ambient sound to improve visual recognition, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to predict sound textures, which falls under the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper mentions using this approach to recognize objects and scenes, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper proposes improvements in the pretext task, which is a machine learning technique, and thus falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
